AREA

static final UnaryOperator.Area AREA
An "identity" operator where the caller is required to pass in the integrated volume between points.

E.g., if the prior measure was "time=10 value=5" and the current measure is "time=20 value=0" then the caller should apply a value of 25.

See Also:
UnaryOperator.Identity
